    <section id="id1166411737452">
      <title>ARS†46-291 Administration and Notice; Locating Deserting Parents</title>
      <para id="id1166416315121">To assist in locating parents who have deserted their children and other persons liable for support of dependents, the Department of Economic Security may request and shall receive information from the records of all departments of this state and its political subdivisions. Notwithstanding any other confidentiality requirement prescribed by law, does the district provide such information as is necessary for this purpose?</para>
      
      
